Introduction

Beauty Box was a girl group under BY-U Entertainment. They made their debut on September 23, 2021, with the single album "Beyond of BB".

BY-U Ent announced that member Jerin had been removed from the group in March of 2023. With reasoning being due to "foreign visa violations" and "reasons attributable to herself as an artist". On May 12, it was revealed that Chaeeun would be joining the group. Later that same month, it was announced that Anh had officially left the group and company due to ongoing health reasons, and Via would be joining the group.

Members Rina and Sara went on hiatus in September. However, fans noticed that their names had been removed from the group's Instagram bio in November of 2023. On All remaining members, with the exception of Via, terminated their exclusive contracts with BY-U on December 2, 2024. In April 2025, Via was introduced as a member of the upcoming group NWH:I, subsequently revealing her departure as well.
